Design and implement a SmartArray class.  A SmartArray:-allows storing a collection of ints.  -has a constructor that takes an int parameter which specifies the maximum number of ints the SmartArray can hold.-Has a method at()  which returns a reference to the int at that index. - Has a method copy() for copying one SmartArray to another.        -throws an exception if you try to access an out-of-bounds index
